modules.description: Computes 32-bit CRC checksums over cstruct buffers or arbitrary segments of strings. Uses the standard CRC-32 algorithm found in Ethernet, ZIP, and PNG formats. Useful for verifying data integrity in network protocols or file formats.

This module computes 32-bit CRC checksums over cstruct buffers or string segments using the standard CRC-32 algorithm found in Ethernet, ZIP, and PNG formats. It supports incremental updates and finalization, enabling efficient integrity checks for streaming data or fixed buffers. For example, it can validate network packets or verify file chunks during transmission. The core types include cstruct buffers and string segments, with operations to initialize, update, and finalize CRC values.
